issue_body:
I'm attempting to get Flower to connect to a RabbitMQ instance on Heroku, but having trouble getting passed the API URL validation.  According to the [Heroku docs](https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/rabbitmq-bigwig#management-api), our URL is mounted at something like `https://bigwig.lshift.net/management/24172/api/`, but we get stuck at [line 96 of `utils/broker.py`](https://github.com/mher/flower/blob/master/flower/utils/broker.py#L95).

```python
    @classmethod
    def validate_http_api(cls, http_api):
        url = urlparse(http_api)
        if url.scheme not in ('http', 'https'):
            raise ValueError("Invalid http api schema: %s" % url.scheme)
        if not url.path.startswith('/api/'):
            raise ValueError("Invalid http api path: %s" % url.path)
```

Kind of wondering if this should just be a warning rather than an exception, or if maybe this was meant to be `endswith()` instead?

This is a feature request that I feel is missing fro dlib's DNN interface. Instead of having the `train` family function taking `std::vector`s like this:

```c++
void train (
    const std::vector<input_type>& data,
    const std::vector<label_type>& labels 
); 
```

it would be nice if an vector like interface was defined, so that the user could get creative on how to get the data to feed the solver, like this:

```c++
template <
    typename vec_type_1,
    typename vec_type_2
>
void train (
    const vec_type_1& data,
    const vec_type_2& labels 
);
```

and the likes for other training family functions (and net evaluation functions). If the `vec_type` interface is specified to fit the std::vector functionalities used by the training functions, it wouldn't break code compatibility, and would allow fancy tricks on how to get the training data, like from a `mmap`ed pointer, or allow the user to attach on-the-fly filters or preprocessors on the data.

Is it desirable? How could it be done? Such a change would be merged? I've posted this to spark some discussion on the issue before I try to implement it.

